*************TO DO**********************

-EITHER MASTER AND SLAVE DEVICE HAVE TO USE shift_reg INTERNALLY FOR SERIAL COMMUNICATION

-TO SUPPORT MULTIDROP BUS SLAVE DEVICES SHOULD USE TRI-STATE OUTPUTS. WITHOUT IT SLAVES CANNOT SHARE A MISO LINE WITH OTHER SLAVES.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*************DATA TRANSMISSION PROGRESS*****************

-TO BEGIN COMMUNICATION, SPI MASTER SELECT THE DEVICE IT WANTS TO COMMUNICATE WITH BY PULLING ITS ssel signal LOW. (ssel: ACTIVE-LOW SIGNAL)

-IF A WAITING PERIOD IS REQUIRED, THE MASTER MUST WAIT FOR AT LEAST A PERIOD OF TIME

-DURING EACH SPI CLOCK CYCLE, THE MASTER SENDS A BIT ON THE MOSI LINE WITH THE SLAVE SENDS A BIT ON THE MISO LINE AND EACH READS THEIR CORRESPONDING INCOMING BIT.

-ON THE CLOCK EDGE, BOTH MASTER AND SLAVE SHIFT OUT A BIT TO ITS COUNTER PARTS.

-EACH RECEIVER SAMPLES THE TRASMITTED BIT AND STORES IT IN THE SHIFT REGISTER AS THE NEW LSB

-AFTER ALL BITS HAVE BEEN SHIFTED OUT AND IN, THE MASTER AND SLAVE HAVE EXCHANGED THEIR REGISTER VALUES. 
 IF MORE DATA NEEDS TO BE EXCHANGED, THE SHIFT REGISTERS ARE RELOADED AND THE PROCESS REPEATS.
 
-WHEN COMPLETE, MASTER STOPS TOGGLING THE CLOCK SIGNAL AND DESELECT SLAVES (ssel<=1)

-EXCEPT THE SELECTED SLAVE, THE OTHERS SHOULD DISREGARD THE INPUT CLOCK AND MOSI SIGNALS. TO PREVENT CONNECTION ON MISO, THESE SLAVES MUST USE TRISTATE OUTPUT.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*************CLOCK POLARITY (CPOL) AND PHASE (CPHA)*****************

-THE MASTER MUST CONFIGURE CLOCK PARITY AND PHASE WITH RESPECT TO THE DATA.

SPI mode---- Clock polarity(CPOL)---- Clock phase(CPHA)------------- Data is shifted out on-------------- Data is sampled on
	0					0						0 			falling SCLK, and when SS activates				rising SCLK
	1					0						1 						rising SCLK							falling SCLK
	2					1						0 			rising SCLK, and when SS activates				falling SCLK
	3					1						1 						falling SCLK						rising SCLK


